Package: SCOPE.CTN
Title: SCOPE (SystematiC prOfiling of disease-relevant sPatial nichEs)
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Yufan", family = "Wu", email = "ywu20@mdanderson.org", role = c("cre", "aut")),
    person(given = "Yutong", family = "Pan", email = "ypan7@mdanderson.org", role = "aut"),
    person(given = "Lulu", family = "Shang", email = "lshang@mdanderson.org", role = "aut"))
Description: A scalable multi-learning statistical framework that represents tissue architecture through Cell type-Triad Niches (CTNs), which are cohort-stable motifs of localized higher-order cell-type interactions. SCOPE integrates multiple spatial colocalization patterns within a multi-view learning framework to derive reusable niche vocabularies from spatially resolved single-cell data. In simulations, SCOPE accurately recovered known niche structures, remained stable under cohort perturbation, and scaled to atlas-level datasets with millions of cells.
